<!--
The smallest beet entry: a script that runs on load and prints, the
`node main.js` shape. `<script>` is a raw-text element so the JavaScript body is
verbatim; `ScriptEntry` fills the entry's action slot (it runs the script and
returns its `console.log` as the response), and `BootOnLoad` calls it once the
entry is built, streaming the output to stdout, then exiting.
-->
<script {(ScriptEntry, BootOnLoad)}>console.log("hello world")</script>
